news.title: Mindspace REIT to add 7-8 million sq ft over next four years
news.para: Mindspace REIT in an interview with ETRealty in September informed about robust 94% occupancy and a 20% re-leasing spread, driven by strong demand from Global Capability Centers and domestic firms. The company is expanding its portfolio organically and through acquisitions, with plans for 7-8 million sq ft under construction.

news.title: Nexus Select Trust to double mall portfolio by FY30; plans ₹5,000-6,000 crore capex via debt-equity mix
news.para: Nexus Select Trust REIT plans to significantly expand its retail portfolio to 18-20 million sq ft across 30-35 malls by FY30. The REIT will fund its ₹5,000-6,000 crore capital needs through debt and equity, leveraging strong portfolio metrics like 98% occupancy and consistent rental growth.

news.title: Odisha RERA to appoint land expert to streamline dispute resolution
news.para: Odisha Real Estate Regulatory Authority is appointing a land expert to help resolve complex property disputes. This move follows the introduction of a new standard operating procedure (SOP) for registering part plots across the state. The new guidelines aim to simplify registrations for family settlements, land transfers, and urban expansions.

news.title: TTDC takes possession of its land housing private hotel in Trichy
news.para: Tamil Nadu Tourism Development Corporation (TTDC) has taken possession of a private star hotel in Trichy for non-payment of lease dues. The hotel, leased on TTDC land since 1994, owed ₹38 crore upon lease expiry. Despite legal challenges, the hotel failed to pay the directed ₹20 crore, leading to the takeover.

news.title: Thiruvananthapuram: Technopark to get new IT spaces, boost for tech sector
news.para: Thiruvananthapuram's IT sector is set for significant growth with new developments across Technopark Phases I, III, and IV, expected to create at least 50,000 jobs. Several new IT buildings and projects, including the World Trade Centre and TCS's new campus, are underway, bolstering the city's IT ecosystem and attracting major enterprises.

news.title: Courts can’t force banks to alter loan terms or grant OTS benefits: Bombay HC
news.para: The Bombay High Court ruled that banks cannot be compelled to offer One-Time Settlement (OTS) benefits or alter loan agreement terms. The court emphasized that such decisions are part of a bank's "commercial wisdom," and borrowers and guarantors are bound by their contractual obligations to repay outstanding amounts.

news.title: All residential complexes in Goa with over 24 units need own STPs
news.para: Goa's pollution control board now mandates sewage treatment plants for residential complexes with 24 or more flats, a reduction from the existing 50-flat rule. This decision follows a scientific study on waste generation and aims to address issues of non-operational STPs. Builders will be responsible for STP maintenance for three years or until handover to the housing society.

news.title: DRA Homes acquires 4.38 acres land in Chennai for ₹50 crore
news.para: DRA Homes has purchased 4.38 acres of land in Chembarambakkam for ₹50 crore. The company plans a one million sq ft residential project. It has an estimated sales potential of ₹650 crore.

news.title: Bombay HC halts flat ‘split’, supports society’s plea
news.para: The Bombay High Court has halted the illegal division of a housing unit into two flats, upholding a society's plea.  The court found no approval for structural changes, deeming the issuance of separate share certificates invalid. This interim order protects other members' rights until a final decision is reached on the flat's unauthorized partition.

news.title: NCLT orders insolvency proceedings against Bhilai Jaypee Cement
news.para: In a significant legal move, the National Company Law Tribunal has launched insolvency proceedings against Bhilai Jaypee Cement, following an outstanding debt of Rs 45 crore to operational creditor Sidhgiri Holdings. The tribunal's admission of the plea signals growing concerns over the company's inability to settle its coal supply bills.

news.title: Real estate, NBFCs lead salary growth in 2026: Aon study
news.para: Salaries in India are projected to rise by nine percent in 2026, led by robust growth in real estate and NBFCs. These sectors are experiencing high talent demand due to government spending and market upcycles. Overall attrition has declined, indicating improved employee stability and retention efforts across organized sectors.

news.title: Private equity investors drive $3.9 billion into Indian real estate in Jan-Sept 2025
news.para: Indian real estate attracted $1.5 billion in private equity during Q3 2025, a 32% dip year-on-year, yet year-to-date inflows remain robust. The office sector led with 39% of investments, closely followed by data centers. Foreign investors are driving over 65% of year-to-date funding, signaling strong confidence in India's long-term real estate prospects.

news.title: About ₹90,000 crore investment to double India's third party data centre capacity by FY28: ICRA
news.para: India's data centre capacity is set to double to 2,400-2,500 MW by FY28, fueled by a massive ₹90,000 crore investment pipeline. Mumbai leads the charge, contributing over half of the current operational capacity.  A proposed 20-year tax exemption policy could significantly boost this growth, making India a stronger player in the global data centre market.

news.title: Cement companies to add 41-43 million MTPA capacity in FY26: ICRA
news.para: A recent GST cut on cement is set to slash rural housing construction costs by up to 1%, making homes more affordable. Cement companies anticipate a 3-5% rise in realization and a 12-18% boost in operating profit per ton for FY26, fueled by robust demand and stable input prices. Green energy adoption is also on the rise.

news.title: GCCs to incrementally lease 50-55 million sq ft during FY26-FY27: ICRA
news.para: Global capability centers are projected to lease 50-55 million sq ft of office space in India's top six cities by FY26-FY27, contributing significantly to overall demand. With over 1,700 GCCs currently, their numbers are expected to surpass 2,500 by 2030, driving substantial revenue and workforce growth.

news.title: About 6.5 lakh illegal properties around Bengaluru to get e-khata under e-swathu drive
news.para: Bengaluru's e-Swathu initiative will provide e-khatas to 6.5 lakh unauthorized properties in gram panchayats, bringing them into the tax net. This aims to regularize over 95 lakh illegal properties statewide, enabling property owners to complete transactions and avail bank loans. The program is expected to significantly boost property tax collections for gram panchayats.

news.title: DDA to hold weekly camps for housing conversion cases in Delhi
news.para: The Delhi Development Authority (DDA) is launching weekly special camps every Thursday to expedite housing conversion cases from leasehold to freehold. These camps, initially held at Vikas Sadan, aim to provide on-the-spot resolution for allottees' queries and document submission, simplifying the process and addressing resident complaints about ownership rights.

news.title: FIR filed against Ocean Seven Buildtech for ₹217 crore housing fraud
news.para: Delhi Police's EOW has filed an FIR against Ocean Seven Buildtech and its MD for allegedly cheating homebuyers and diverting Rs 217 crore from the incomplete Expressway Towers project. Buyers accuse the developer of misrepresentation and fraudulent resale of units, while the developer denies fraud, citing pandemic and NGT restrictions for delays.

news.title: Duroply eyes 15–18% growth in FY26; to ramp West & South markets
news.para: Duroply Industries anticipates 15-18% year-on-year growth, confident in achieving its 15% revenue target for FY25. The company leverages an asset-light model and contract manufacturing, expecting policy changes and improving macroeconomics to drive sector growth. Duroply is also investing in brand building and exploring AI for quality control.
